'''Acanthodii''' is an {{Rarity|Unusual}} fish found in the [[Ancient Isle]].

== Description ==
{{Description|Acanthodii, commonly known as Spiny Sharks, possess many scales that form a diamond pattern along its body. They prey on smaller creatures among the Ancient Isle's waters, and are active both during the day and night. They went extinct around 250 million years ago, at the end of the Permian period.|Bestiary Entry}}

